entry.title: Hydrologic Outlook issued May 25 at 1:54PM MDT by NWS
entry.summary: ...Expect Increased Flows on the Green River Below Flaming Gorge Reservoir Due to Releases... Releases from Flaming Gorge Reservoir have started to increase today May 24 and will reach to around 8600 cfs by the morning of May 26. The 8600 cfs release is scheduled to last for 7 days before starting to ramp down.

entry.title: Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 9:21PM CDT by NWS
entry.summary: ...PATCHY DENSE FOG EXPECTED ALONG THE LAKE MICHIGAN SHORELINE... Areas of fog will impact the lakeshore counties into the overnight hours, and may become dense at times close to the shoreline. Visibilities could be reduced to a quarter mile or less in spots, which will result in locally hazardous driving conditions. Motorists should be alert for fog and rapidly changing visibilities.
